Depends: ipmitool, kmod, openipmi, {{ DEPS }}
Description: generic temperature-driven fan controller over local IPMI
 A lightweight bash daemon that regulates server fan speed from temperature,
 through the local IPMI interface (/dev/ipmi0).
 .
 Self-adapting: it discovers temperature sensors and their own Upper-Critical
 thresholds, then normalizes the speed curve per sensor, so nothing is
 hard-coded and it works across CPUs and servers.
 .
 Writing the fan speed uses an auto-detected vendor profile (ipmitool mc info).
 Dell iDRAC is supported; any unrecognized vendor falls back to monitor mode
 (read-only) and never touches the fans. Fan regulation is handed back to the
 BMC automatically on over-temperature, a failed fan, or loss of IPMI
 communication.
